UBS Board to Meet as Banking Head Kengeter Pledges Review of Risk Controls

-- B y   G i l e s   B r o o m   a n d   A m b e r e e n   C h o u d h u r y
-- 
2011-09-19T16:01:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-19/ubs-board-said-to-plan-meeting-after-2-3-billion-trading-loss.html
UBS AG (UBSN) ’s directors will meet in
 Singapore  later this week following the lender’s disclosure of a
$2.3 billion loss from unauthorized trading, according to two
people with knowledge of the situation.  The board will discuss the loss and review possible
management changes, said one of the people who declined to be
identified because the discussions are private. Officials at the
Zurich-based bank declined to comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Giles Broom in Zurich at 
 gbroom@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at 
 eevans3@bloomberg.net  